{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 · G6 (approach soundness) — PASS, no findings. Mechanism is sound and grounded: planned-trace (not result) parity is the correct choice for LLM-variable output; the FakeRunner/intended-model capture, pre-escalation tolerance, flag-gated cutover (verify.gate_engine), and reuse of shared sizing/pass1 units behind epic A's batch-runner seam all match the real engine implementation (workflow/trace.py, gate_dispatch.py, production_batch_runner.py, gates/*.yaml). Considered alternatives (result-parity; big-bang cutover) — both inferior on robustness/blast-radius and the plan defensibly avoids them. Positive rationale is present throughout."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782507496028594001,"uuid":"45d2b28a-849e-4b61-8130-1c5bf9d1d0f8"}